  "summary": "Postinstall beacon exfiltrating host information and environment variables",
  "details": "Package declares a postinstall hook (`\"postinstall\": \"node run.js\"`) that runs automatically on `npm install`. The tarball ships beacon scripts (`beacon34.js`, `beacon_linux.js`) that import `child_process`, `os`, `http`, and `https`, read host identifiers (`os.hostname()`, `os.platform()`, `process.platform`) and environment variables (`process.env`), and emit outbound HTTP `GET`/`POST` / `http.request(...)` calls. The package's only stated effect is this beacon — it is a host-reconnaissance and environment-exfiltration payload that fires unattended at install time. There is no legitimate library functionality.",
